# Spellbook v1.0.0 Test Coverage Plan

## Phase 1 — Persistence (must-have for v1.0.0)
Target: `src/archivist/archivist.rs`

- [ ] Archivist::load / save round-trip for Codex
- [ ] load assigns UUIDs to spells with empty id
- [ ] load rejects invalid codex via validate_codex
- [ ] save uses atomic write (tmp file cleaned up)
- [ ] load_theme / save_theme round-trip
- [ ] load_theme returns default when file missing
- [ ] load_user_settings / save_user_settings round-trip
- [ ] load_recents / save_recents round-trip
- [ ] export_codex produces valid TOML that import_codex can reload
- [ ] export_spellbook exports only the selected book + its spells
- [ ] import_codex validates imported data
- [ ] merge_codex with all three strategies (Skip, Overwrite, Rename)
- [ ] append_spell adds a spell to existing codex
- [ ] append_spellbook adds a spellbook to existing codex

## Phase 2 — State mutations (must-have)
Target: `src/state.rs`

- [ ] add_spell adds spell to codex and assigns to spellbook
- [ ] add_spellbook adds a new spellbook
- [ ] delete_spellbook removes book but keeps spells
- [ ] save persists codex to disk
- [ ] recents survive a load round-trip

## Phase 3 — Browse/navigation logic (high-value)
Targets:
- `src/ui/browse_spellbooks.rs`
- `src/ui/browse_spells.rs`
- `src/ui/form.rs`
- `src/ui/jobs.rs`

- [ ] browse_spellbooks: arrow navigation wraps correctly
- [ ] browse_spellbooks: Enter opens selected spellbook
- [ ] browse_spellbooks: search filter updates visible indices
- [ ] browse_spellbooks: command palette opens with ':'
- [ ] browse_spells: up/down wraps at list boundaries
- [ ] browse_spells: Enter copies selected spell
- [ ] browse_spells: edit trigger ('e') opens edit form
- [ ] browse_spells: favorite toggle ('f') flips flag
- [ ] browse_spells: execute modes (simple/TUI/background)
- [ ] form: Tab/BackTab cycles fields
- [ ] form: Ctrl+S saves spell/spellbook
- [ ] form: Esc cancels (with unsaved-changes warning)
- [ ] form: dropdown navigation in spellbook field
- [ ] jobs: Up/Down changes selected job
- [ ] jobs: kill/cancel/dismiss with initialized JobManager

## Phase 4 — Supporting modules (nice-to-have)
Targets:
- `src/clipboard.rs`
- `src/ui/confirm.rs`
- `src/ui/input.rs`
- `src/ui/quick_add_spell.rs`
- `src/editor.rs`

- [ ] clipboard: ExecutionResult display stdout/stderr truncation
- [ ] clipboard: save_to_file output format
- [ ] confirm: requires_typed_confirmation per action
- [ ] confirm: title and confirmation_word per action
- [ ] input: substitute replaces placeholders
- [ ] input: validate requires all placeholders filled
- [ ] quick_add_spell: field navigation and save flow
- [ ] quick_add_spell: dropdown index maps to spellbook index
- [ ] editor: resolve_editor priority and fallback behavior

## Phase 5 — Test infrastructure

- [ ] Extend or add shared test helpers in `src/test_utils.rs`
- [ ] Helper: isolated temporary codex/theme/settings/recents files
- [ ] Helper: deterministic State for archivist tests (no ~/.spellbook)
- [ ] Document test helper usage in AGENTS.md

## Notes

- Default view mode is now Cards (verified in theme tests).
- Use `State::new_test()` for isolated unit tests; keep `State::new()` for production + integration tests.
- All new tests must run with `nix develop --command cargo test`.
